ol.li:
 The actual observation is preferably coded in LOINC (subset as defined by FPS Health)
"code":{
	"coding":[
		{
			"system": "http://loinc.org",
			"code": "30341-2",
			"display": "Erythrocyte sedimentation rate"
		}
		]
	}

 If above not possible , ALBERT codes are used (subset as defined by FPS Health) 

"code":{
	"coding":[
		{
			"system": "https://www.ehealth.fgov.be/standards/fhir/CodeSystem/albert",
			"code": "26224",
			"display": "Glucose (urine 24h)"
		}
		]
	}

 If above not possible,laboratory sends its own code plus obligatory a text element to further explain.
"code":{
	"coding":[
		{
			"system": "OWNSYSTEM",
			"code": "OWNCODE",
			"display": "DISPLAYOWNCODE"
		}
		],
	"text": "TEXTEXPLAINING"
	}

 If above not possible the kind of observation is expressed only in text (allowed but not recommended)
"code":{
	"text": "TEXTEXPLAINING"
	}

div.p:
If needed, it is always possible to add extra translations in the display using the HL7 translation extension as such"code":{
         "coding": [
           {
             "system": "http://loinc.org",
             "code": "18723-7",
             "display": "Hematology studies (set)",
             "_display": {
               "extension": [
                 {
                   "url": "http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/translation",
                   "extension": [
                     {
                       "url": "lang",
                       "valueCode": "be-nl"
                     },
                     {
                       "url": "content",
                       "valueString": "HEMATOLOGIE"
                     }
                   ]
                 }
               ]
             }
           }
         ]
       }
